Corvid uses dSFMT ver. 2.2.3, the double precision SIMD-oriented Fast Mersenne 
Twister (dSFMT).  
Copyright (c) 2011,2002 Mutsuo Saito, Makoto Matsumoto and Hiroshima
University. All rights reserved.  See the license for this code (available
on the internet) for further information.

Corvid uses the bnldev and gammln functions (both in bnldev.c) from 
Numerical Recipes in C.  
Copyright 1988-1992 by Cambridge University Press.
